aineruniface_104bsu1665702614517.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bsu1665702614517.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bsu1665702614517.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bsu1665702614517\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Controls whether the language-specific input mode in the Input Method Editor (IME) is\n    disabled when the GOLD key is used.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__topic_d146150e1_d146151e1_d146152e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__p_d146153e1_d146154e1_d146155e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">AutoImeGold</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__section_lz1_p14_yvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d994432e67\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__ul_rxr_p14_yvb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__li_d51017e1_d51018e1_d51019e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>—switch the IME to direct input\n          mode when the GOLD key is used. Once the complete GOLD key sequence has been entered, the\n          IME is returned to its previous state. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__li_d51020e1_d51021e1_d51022e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>—IME remains the same when the\n          GOLD key is used. </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bsu1665702614517__table_d17855e1_d17856e1_d17857e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">File section</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzj1665702614359.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzj1665702614359.html\" title=\"The [upi] section of the initialization file determines the appearance or behavior of many Universal Presentation Interface (UPI) objects under Microsoft Windows.\">[upi]</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pvy1665702614635.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>AutoImeOpen</a><p>Enable the Input Method Editor (IME) for string fields for which the input mode has not been explicitly defined (by the field syntax YIME (IME on) or NIME (IME off)).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526219\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526219\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "AutoImeGold Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 25, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Controls whether the language-specific input mode in the Input Method Editor (IME) is disabled when the GOLD key is used. AutoImeGold = on | off Arguments on —switch the IME to direct input mode when the GOLD key is used. Once the complete GOLD key sequence has been entered, the IME is returned to its previous state. off —IME remains the same when the GOLD key is used. Default value on File section [upi] Related Links AutoImeOpen Enable the Input Method Editor (IME) for string fields for which the input mode has not been explicitly defined (by the field syntax YIME (IME on) or NIME (IME off)). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}